metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #169
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: Altered #21
metadata.description:
Adj. Changed in character or composition, typically in a comparatively small but significant way.

Please note that the display is progressive and can take some time to finalize.

Artwork by Patrice Orenes-Lerma - @patxol - 2022
Made with math, love & p5js.
CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Features include :

- 20 color palettes (10 standard, 10 rare)
- 8 palette progression types
- 3 aspect ratio (Portrait is standard, 1:1 and landscape are rare)
- 8 Alteration types
- 3 Alteration power levels
- 5 types of symmetry
- 3 densities
- Spaced mode and Sharp mode

metadata.name: Whirlwind #16
metadata.description:
The circle is divided into rings. 
The rings are divided into arcs. 
The whirlwind then colors and twists the arcs.

Variations:
- 1 circle on the screen
- grid of circles 2 by 2, 3 by 3
- several circles in the center of different radius
- the circles are arranged in the form of rays from the center

Dark/light background
Gradient/organized/chaotic colors of arcs
Organized/chaotic thickness of arcs

Please be patient. It takes a long time to generate. Thanks.

________
by neigal 24.05.2022

metadata.name: Sun #33
metadata.description:
Sun has emerged through many many tests to emphasize contrasts. One of those tests has generated some kind of star pattern with a halo of high brightness and a more chaotic and constrasted surface. A reminiscent light in the very center and a background made of projecting brightness have also appeared during the creating process. In fact, it was even more close to the beginning of the imploding step of a star than its daily life !

Then, playing around with randomness, I have discovered that there was a large panel of possibilities going from the early stage of the implosion to the black hole occurence. Adding colors palettes and deformations have led to a complete project.

I hope you will enjoy those pieces as much as me !

metadata.name: Celestial Objects #65
metadata.description:
Celestial Objects is a generative collection imagining planets and stars in the space, with light and shadows being key themes. 

The artwork is primarily rendered using hundreds of thousands of points (more than a million in some cases) to create different aspects of the output including the sky textures, shooting stars and shadows on the planets. 

Celestial Objects is coded in p5.js, and please note that it takes 5-15 seconds for each output to render.

Controls (in live view): 
Press [2] to render 2000x2000px image
Press [4] to render 4000x4000px image
Press [s] to save the current view (default window size or 2000px or 4000px image)
